keyWord:cruel
keyWord:harshness
keyWord:cutthroat
keyWord:ruthless
noun:The kind of attitude or action in which people all want the same thing and do not care if they harm each other in getting it. English = ruthlessness.
noun:Behaviour that deliberately causes pain or distress to people or animals. English = cruelty, abuse, harshness.
verbOrAdjective:To be the kind of attitude or action in which people all want the same thing and do not care if they harm each other in getting it. English = (be) cutthroat, (be) ruthless.
verbOrAdjective:To be cruel and violent. English = (be) vicious.
verbOrAdjective:To behave in a way that deliberately causes pain or distress to people or animals. English = (be) cruel.
